{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## AEROCOM default regions (class `Region`)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook introduces how pya handles information related to default regions (e.g. Europe, Asia, ...) as used in the [AEROCOM interface](http://aerocom.met.no/cgi-bin/AEROCOM/aerocom/surfobs_annualrs.pl). All default regions are defined in the file [regions.ini](http://aerocom.met.no/pya/config_files.html#default-regions)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Initating pyaerocom configuration\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Checking database access...\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Checking access to: /lustre/storeA\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Access to lustre database: True\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Init data paths for lustre\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Expired time: 0.016 s\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import pyaerocom as pya"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### What regions are available"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "['WORLD',\n",
       " 'EUROPE',\n",
       " 'ASIA',\n",
       " 'AUSTRALIA',\n",
       " 'CHINA',\n",
       " 'INDIA',\n",
       " 'NAFRICA',\n",
       " 'SAFRICA',\n",
       " 'SAMERICA',\n",
       " 'NAMERICA']"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pya.region.all()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "These region IDs can be used to access more information about the regions (which is used throughout pyaerocom). For instance:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Create a `Region`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "pyaeorocom Region\n",
      "Name: EUROPE\n",
      "Longitude range: [-20, 70]\n",
      "Latitude range: [30, 80]\n",
      "Longitude range (plots): [-20, 70]\n",
      "Latitude range (plots): [30, 80]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "europe = pya.Region(\"EUROPE\")\n",
    "print(europe)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "pyaeorocom Region\n",
      "Name: ASIA\n",
      "Longitude range: [40, 150]\n",
      "Latitude range: [0, 60]\n",
      "Longitude range (plots): [40, 150]\n",
      "Latitude range (plots): [0, 60]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "asia = pya.Region(\"ASIA\")\n",
    "print(asia)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Load example data and apply region specific crop\n",
    "\n",
    "In the following cell, we create an instance of the `GriddedData` class (hich is introduced in more detail in a later tutorial), load some test data (from the CAMS ECMWF OSUITE dataset), crop it and plot a map of the results over Europe."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Overwriting unit unknown in cube od550aer with value \"1\"\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x576 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "data = pya.GriddedData()\n",
    "data._init_testdata_default()\n",
    "crop = data.crop(region=\"EUROPE\")\n",
    "fig = crop.quickplot_map()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Computing distance to centre of region\n",
    "\n",
    "For a given lat / lon coordinate, distances to the region centre coordinate can be computed as:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "3476.358401761219"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dc = asia.distance_to_center(lat=45, lon=60)\n",
    "dc #km"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Access centre coordinate:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(30.0, 95.0)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "asia.center_coordinate # (lat, lon)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "0.0"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "asia.distance_to_center(30, 95)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "That's it. Not much more to say about regions until now."
   ]
  }
 ],
